messages.content: What is the recommended number of steps for the Kohaku_LoNyu_Yog sampler?
The recommended number of steps for the Kohaku_LoNyu_Yog sampler is 10 steps.
Why does the Kohaku_LoNyu_Yog sampler perform slower compared to other methods?
The Kohaku_LoNyu_Yog sampler performs slower than other methods because it is a second-order method.
In which model does the Euler Negative and Euler dy Negative samplers perform better?
The Euler Negative and Euler dy Negative samplers perform slightly better in the SDXL model.
What is the purpose of the Euler Smea Dyn Sampler?
The Euler Smea Dyn Sampler is a sampling method based on Euler's approach, designed to generate superior imagery.
How does the SMEA sampler improve image quality?
The SMEA sampler can significantly mitigate structural and limb collapse when generating large images and can produce superior hand depictions.
Which model performs very well with the SMEA sampler?
The SMEA sampler performs very well in the SD1.5 model.
How much more computational resources does the Euler SMEA Dy sampler consume compared to the Euler dy?
The Euler SMEA Dy sampler consumes approximately 1.25 times more computational resources than the Euler dy.
